    <item>
      <title>Fix shell injection in validate-frontmatter workflow</title>
      <link>https://github.com/anthropics/claude-plugins-official/commit/068a59e000f2aa4f0dee0fc5bb4d196c6120a3e6</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">068a59e</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 00:38:18 GMT</pubDate>
      <category>gh-commits-plugins-official</category>
      <description>The &apos;Validate frontmatter&apos; step interpolated step output directly into a double-quoted shell string, allowing a fork PR that adds a file named e.g. agents/$(curl ...).md to execute arbitrary commands on the runner.  - Pass the file list via env: and reference as &quot;$FILES&quot; so the shell   never re-eval</description>
    </item>
